@startuml diag_stage_to_ethb_service_security_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Diag Stage To ETHB Service Security Signal Flow\n(route/boundary diag stage -> ETHB route-health and security-level publish)

participant "NAV / notif /\nboundary context" as DiagCtx #F4F7FB
participant "ETHB\nbackbone state owner" as ETHB #E8F7E8
participant "Backbone service state" as BackboneBus #FFF4CC
participant "Observers / diagnostics" as Obs #E8F0FE

== Backbone Inputs ==

DiagCtx -> ETHB : nav session / route class\nalert level\nboundaryAlive\nwarningPathStatus\nfailSafeMode
ETHB -> ETHB : roadZoneActive / guidedRouteActive
ETHB -> ETHB : serviceContext = ethHasBoundaryServiceContext(...)
ETHB -> ETHB : diagStage = ethDiagBoundaryStage(...)
note right of ETHB
Representative inputs
- roadZoneActive / guidedRouteActive
- boundaryAlive
- warningPathStatus
- failSafeMode
- alertLevel
end note

== Service / Security Publish ==

ETHB -> ETHB : routeHealth / serviceHealth / securityLevel / activeServices / faultBitmap
ETHB -> BackboneBus : backbone mode / route health / service health / security level
note right of ETHB
Representative outputs
- backboneMode
- routeHealth
- serviceHealth
- securityLevel
- faultBitmap
end note

== Downstream Visibility ==

BackboneBus -> Obs : backbone route/service/security readback

note over DiagCtx, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. Route, alert, and boundary context reach ETHB
2. ETHB derives diagnostic stage and service context
3. ETHB publishes route health and security level on the backbone state path
4. Observers and diagnostics consume the effective backbone posture
end note

@enduml
